@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'QuadriCon' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
4 colours.

                             How to play?

  When first run, QuadriCon will briefly display a pattern just to
show how the links should be placed, after that, the game shuffles
the links and it is up to you to recreate that shape...

  To play, click on any octagonal-shaped tile, if there is at least
one link connected to the tile, it will rotate clockwise by 90
degrees around that tile. Note that you cannot click on the small
dots that are located at various places on the game board.
Sometimes, the small dots are placed in such a way that they are
part of the shape to match.

  A '@{b}?@{ub}' button appears on the lower left in the game window,
clicking on this button (or pressing on the 'Help' key) will
briefly display the shape to match and then will redisplay the
game board as you left it.

  The colour of the links can be changed by clicking on the button
that contains a coloured cross, located on the lower right of the
game board.

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the New Game button.

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's close button or
press the 'Esc' key.

